Program: The History Hour
Title: When Homosexuality Was a Crime
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p059f799
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 30 Jul 2017
Comedian and broadcaster Pete Price speaks about being subjected to horrific aversion therapy to "cure" him of his homosexuality in 1960s Britain. Plus the 99-year-old former aide to the Chinese nationalist leader, Chiang Kai Shek, a radical new approach to housing in the former USSR, the perils of deep sea commercial diving in the North Sea and how the Welsh fought for recognition of their language. Photo: Pete Price (private collection) Show less